{"parse":{"title":"Local operational picture","pageid":21915258,"revid":818675280,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"plainlinks metadata ambox ambox-style ambox-Context\" role=\"presentation\"><tbody><tr><td class=\"mbox-image\"><div style=\"width:52px\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/40px-Edit-clear.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/60px-Edit-clear.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/f/f2/Edit-clear.svg/80px-Edit-clear.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"48\" data-file-height=\"48\" /></div></td><td class=\"mbox-text\"><div class=\"mbox-text-span\">This article <b>provides insufficient context for those unfamiliar with the subject</b>.<span class=\"hide-when-compact\"> Please help <a class=\"external text\" href=\"//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Local_operational_picture&amp;action=edit\">improve the article</a> with a <a href=\"/wiki/Wikipedia:Writing_better_articles#Lead_section\" title=\"Wikipedia:Writing better articles\">good introductory style</a>.</span>  <small><i>(October 2009)</i></small><small class=\"hide-when-compact\"><i> (<a href=\"/wiki/Help:Maintenance_template_removal\" title=\"Help:Maintenance template removal\">Learn how and when to remove this template message</a>)</i></small></div></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<table role=\"presentation\" class=\"mbox-small plainlinks sistersitebox\" style=\"background-color:#f9f9f9;border:1px solid #aaa;color:#000\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<td class=\"mbox-image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/40px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png\" width=\"40\" height=\"40\" class=\"noviewer\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/60px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/99/Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg/80px-Wiktionary-logo-en-v2.svg.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"512\" data-file-height=\"512\" /></td>\n<td class=\"mbox-text plainlist\">Look up <i><b><a href=\"https://en.wiktionary.org/wiki/local_operational_picture\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wiktionary:local operational picture\">local operational picture</a></b></i> in Wiktionary, the free dictionary.</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>A <b>local operational picture</b> (<b>LOP</b>) is a single identical display of relevant (operational) information of the <a href=\"/wiki/Battlespace\" title=\"Battlespace\">battlespace</a> (e.g. position of own troops and enemy troops, position and status of important infrastructure such as bridges, roads, etc.) constructed for local use.\n</p><p>A LOP is an emerging military concept.  Although, there are literary examples that suggests that a LOP is for the use of a <a href=\"/wiki/Platoon\" title=\"Platoon\">platoon</a> <a href=\"/wiki/Commander\" title=\"Commander\">commander</a> and its coverage range is 250 meter radius.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>  A <b>LOP</b> assists a platoon commander to achieve <i><a href=\"/wiki/Situational_awareness\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Situational awareness\">situational awareness</a></i>.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Relationship_to_the_COP\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Relationship to the COP</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Construction\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Construction</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Further_reading\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Further reading</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Relationship_to_the_COP\">Relationship to the COP</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Local_operational_picture&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Relationship to the COP\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Various LOPs may be shared electronically and fused into <a href=\"/wiki/Common_operational_picture\" title=\"Common operational picture\">common operational picture</a> (COP). Generally, sharing the <b>LOP</b> to form a COP implies that the LOP is replaced by the COP and hence has limited duration.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Construction\">Construction</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Local_operational_picture&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Construction\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>A LOP is constructed with the aid of platform mounted/dismounted <a href=\"/wiki/Sensor\" title=\"Sensor\">sensors</a> that determine <a href=\"/wiki/Geographic_coordinate_system\" title=\"Geographic coordinate system\">geo position</a> and signatures.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Local_operational_picture&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Battlespace\" title=\"Battlespace\">Battlespace</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sensor_fusion\" title=\"Sensor fusion\">Sensor fusion</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Almirante_Clemente_class_destroyer#Sensors_Signatures\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Almirante Clemente class destroyer\">Almirante Clemente class destroyer#Sensors Signatures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/U.S._Military_M274_Truck,_Platform,_Utility_1/2_Ton,_4X4\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"U.S. Military M274 Truck, Platform, Utility 1/2 Ton, 4X4\">U.S. Military M274 Truck, Platform, Utility 1/2 Ton, 4X4</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Local_operational_picture&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">\"Challenge # 30: Local operational picture: Improving local area awareness\", Candidate Design Challenge 7 Submissions, <a href=\"/wiki/Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology\" title=\"Massachusetts Institute of Technology\">Massachusetts Institute of Technology</a>\nSoldier Design Competition VI, Academic Year 2008-2009 <cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.is/20110529135732/http://18.125.1.109/sdc/Challenge30.htm\">\"Archived copy\"</a>. Archived from <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://18.125.1.109/sdc/Challenge30.htm\">the original</a> on 2011-05-29<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2009-03-11</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_v